text: Oreopanax stenophyllus is an evergreen shrub or treelet in the family Araliaceae. It is endemic to cloud forests on the eastern slopes of the Peruvian Andes, between 2800 and 3700 meters above sea level. ==References== Category:Flora of Peru stenophyllus Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
title: Oreopanax stenophyllus
